  "num": "N10",
  "question": "<p>Using your answer to the previous question, explain why an overflow error has occurred when adding these two register values (200 and 100) together.</p>",
  "caseStudy": "<p>A simple 8-bit microcontroller stores every value it works with — sensor readings, counters, and the results of calculations — inside 8-bit registers. Each register can hold any whole denary number from 0 to 255, represented internally in pure binary.</p>",
  "hint": "Think about the maximum value an 8-bit register can actually hold, and where the extra bit from the addition has to go.",
