   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\">\n<h5>Mark Scheme — 2 marks (1 mark per point)</h5>\n<ul>\n<li>The true result of the addition, 300, is greater than 255 — the largest denary value an 8-bit register can store</li>\n<li>The addition produces a carry out of the left-most (128) column / needs a 9th bit, and the 8-bit register has nowhere to store it</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"marks-section\">\n<h5>How the marks are given</h5>\n<ul>\n<li>Accept either point made in the student's own words, provided it correctly links the register's 8-bit limit to the size of the true result.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>",
