  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Thinking a colour depth of n bits gives n possible colours — e.g. assuming 4 bits means 4 colours.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> It is <strong>2 to the power of n</strong>, not n. A colour depth of 4 bits gives 2<sup>4</sup> = <strong>16</strong> possible colours, not 4. Each extra bit DOUBLES the number of colours available, rather than adding a fixed amount.</p>",
