  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Leaving a file-size calculation answer in bits, because the multiplication already produced 'a number' that looks like an answer.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Colour depth × height × width always gives the answer in <strong>bits</strong> first — that is only the first step. You must then divide by 8 to reach bytes, and keep dividing by 1,000 for each unit up the ladder until you reach the unit the question actually asked for.</p>",
