  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Believing the Copyright Act protects computer systems from hackers.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> The <strong>Copyright, Designs and Patents Act</strong> protects <strong>original work</strong> (software, music, images, writing) from being <strong>copied</strong>. Protecting <strong>systems</strong> from being <strong>hacked</strong> is the <strong>Computer Misuse Act</strong>. One is about copying work; the other is about breaking in.</p>",
  "question": "Which law is broken by illegally copying and distributing a piece of paid-for software?",
