  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Believing computational thinking is only relevant once you are already writing code.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Computational thinking is used <strong>before</strong> code is written, to plan and simplify a solution — and it applies to solving <em>any</em> complex problem, not only programming ones.</p>",
