  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Thinking an algorithm and algorithmic thinking are the same thing.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> <strong>Algorithmic thinking</strong> is the thinking <em>process</em> of working out the steps needed. An <strong>algorithm</strong> is the <em>result</em> — the finished sequence of steps itself.</p>",
