  "source": "learn",
  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Completing an algorithm",
  "reading": "<h4>Filling in a missing line or condition</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>\"Complete the algorithm\" questions give you a working algorithm with one or more lines <strong>missing</strong>, and ask you to supply exactly what belongs there so it does what is described.</li>\n<li>Method: work out what the SURROUNDING lines need to be true. Match variable names already in use exactly, and check loop/condition boundaries carefully — off-by-one is the most common slip.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"code-block\">total = 0\nfor i = 1 to ____        // must repeat 5 times → \"5\"\n  total = total + i\nnext i\nprint(____)               // must show the result → \"total\"</div>",
