  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Thinking every error that stops a program from working must be a 'logic error'.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> A <strong>logic</strong> error still RUNS — it just gives the wrong result. An error that stops the program running at all (like a missing <code>endif</code>) is a <strong>syntax</strong> error, because it breaks the rules of the language.</p>",
