  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Thinking 'refining' an algorithm means fixing a mistake in it.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> Refining assumes the algorithm <strong>already works correctly</strong>. It means making it <strong>better</strong> — more efficient, more readable, or able to handle more cases — without changing what it does. Fixing a mistake so it works correctly is <strong>correcting</strong> it, a different step.</p>",
  "question": "An algorithm already gives the correct answer. A programmer rewrites it to be shorter and easier to read. What is this called?",
