  "pageId": "computer-science:2-2-3a-string-manipulation",
  "pageName": "2.2.3a String Manipulation",
  "source": "misc",
  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Thinking concatenation with + automatically inserts a space, or converts a number to a string automatically.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> <code>+</code> joins strings <strong>exactly as they are</strong> — you must add any spaces yourself, using <code>\" \"</code>. Joining a string with a number often needs the number <strong>converted to a string first</strong>, or the program may cause an error.</p>",
  "question": "name = \"Sam\"  and  age = 12 . Which line correctly prints  \"Sam is 12\" ?",
