  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Thinking .upper or .lower permanently changes the original string in place.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> <code>str.upper</code> and <code>str.lower</code> each <strong>return a new string</strong> — they do <strong>not</strong> change the variable they were called on. To keep the result, you must store it back: <code>str = str.upper</code>.</p>",
