  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Thinking string indexing starts at 1, the way people usually count things.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> ERL strings are <strong>0-indexed</strong>, exactly like arrays: the first character is always at index <strong>0</strong>. For <code>word = \"Cat\"</code>, the valid indices are <code>0, 1, 2</code> — there is no index 3.</p>",
