  "pageId": "computer-science:2-2-3b-arrays",
  "pageName": "2.2.3b Arrays",
  "source": "learn",
  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "2D arrays — a grid of rows and columns",
  "reading": "<h4>Storing table-shaped data</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>A <strong>2D array</strong> stores data arranged as a <strong>grid</strong> — rows and columns — useful for anything table-shaped, such as a seating plan, a spreadsheet, or a game board.</li>\n<li>It is declared with <strong>two</strong> sizes: <code>array grid[3,4]</code> declares a grid with <strong>3 rows</strong> and <strong>4 columns</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"code-block\">array grid[3,4]     // 3 rows, 4 columns — 12 elements in total</div>",
