  "source": "learn",
  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "What SQL in J277 can and can't do",
  "reading": "<h4>J277 SQL is for reading data, not changing it</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>For OCR J277 you only need to <strong>read</strong> data using SELECT, FROM and WHERE — this is sometimes called <strong>querying</strong>.</li>\n<li>You do <strong>not</strong> need commands that add, change or delete data (such as INSERT, UPDATE or DELETE) — they are outside the J277 specification.</li>\n<li>Running a SELECT query never changes anything stored in the table — it only returns a <strong>view</strong> of the data that matches the query.</li>\n</ul>",
