  "source": "exam",
  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "num": "Q2",
  "question": "<p>A program uses <strong>random(3, 7)</strong> to pick a value. Tick <strong>one</strong> box to identify a value it can NEVER return.</p>",
  "options": [
   "8",
   "3",
   "5",
   "7, because the upper value given to random is sometimes wrongly thought to be included as a possible result when it should actually be excluded"
  ],
  "hint": "random(a, b) is inclusive of both a and b — everything from 3 up to 7 is possible.",
