  "pageName": "2.2.3e Sub Programs and Random Numbers",
  "source": "misc",
  "type": "mcq",
  "marks": 1,
  "readingTitle": "Misconception check",
  "reading": "<p><strong>❌ Common misconception:</strong> Thinking a procedure can return a value, just like a function can.</p><p><strong>✅ The correct idea:</strong> A <strong>procedure</strong> performs a task but does <strong>not</strong> return a value — it has no <code>return</code> statement. If a value needs to be sent back to wherever the sub program was called from, it must be written as a <strong>function</strong> instead.</p>",
